'''Murkhana Landing''' was a hexagonal shaped [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]] linked to [[Murkhana City/Legends|Murkhana City]] by four ten-kilometer-long bridges. The platform was supported by thick columns anchored in the sea bed. It was a key target of [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] forces during the [[Battle of Murkhana (Clone Wars)|Battle of Murkhana]] in the final days of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. Led by [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Jedi Master/Legends|Master]] [[Roan Shryne]] and [[Clone Commander/Legends|Clone Commander]] [[Salvo (clone trooper)|Salvo]], along with Master [[Bol Chatak]] and her [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Olee Starstone]], the [[32nd Air Combat Wing]] were sent in to disable a [[Deflector shield generator/Legends|deflector shield generator]] that was housed in the lower levels of a medcenter, which protected the landing with overlapping [[Particle shield/Legends|particle shields]]. With the assistance of the [[Clone commando/Legends|clone commando]] unit of [[Ion Team]], the Jedi were able to destroy the generator, paving the way for Republic, and eventually [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] control.

